-- MOVES-Old Mutual's fund manager Bradbury to retire
-- By Carolyn Cohn
-- Tue Sep 23, 2014 08:15AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Old Mutual Global Investors said on Tuesday that fund manager Ashton Bradbury will retire at the end of the year.

Tim Service, deputy fund manager of the investment firm's UK specialist equity hedge fund, will become co-manager of the fund and take over the running of the fund after Bradbury's retirement, the firm said in a statement.